<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="type specimen">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Type specimen.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
MCZ 271976. We tried to find this lot in the MCZ with the help of Mr. Cleo Oliveira, but the curators could not find it. We made contact with Dr John A. Allen who sent us live specimens from Surinam Basin #293 (08°58'N54°04'W, 1518 m) to compare with Campos Basin specimens. Furthermore, using the good description in 
<bibRefCitation author="Sanders, HL" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="237 - 261" title="Studies on the deep sea Protobranchia (Bivalvia): Prologue and the Pristiglomidae." volume="145" year="1973">Sanders and Allen (1973)</bibRefCitation>
and figures of the specimens of Rockall Trough and Biscay Bay available in 
<bibRefCitation pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Oliver et al. (2009)</bibRefCitation>
we could properly identify our specimens.
</paragraph>
